				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree with the AA suggestion.   I really like the one where it is suggested that you first kill the mob, then your Warder assumes the attributes of that mob.  Very innovative idea.
<br />
As for pet class, melee class, pure caster, impure caster...does it really matter?  No point in arguing it.  I recall personally whining against Verant when the arguably "bastardized" class of Beastlord was introduced as a Hybrid.
<br />
I argued vehemently that in reality we were a True Pet Class and should not be treated (and penalized the same way) as a Hybrid class.  That was shot down and shot down hard by Verant/SOE.
<br />
I do recognize that a Beastlord is:
<br />

<br />
A retarded Monk.
<br />
A retarded Shaman.
<br />
A very good Pet manager.
<br />

<br />
