<br />

<br />
We get the best Monk disc - Stonestance. (Otherwise known to us as Protective Spirit.  The messaging for that disc was actually identical to Stonestance the first year or so, and the <span style="font-style: italic">effect</span> is still identical.)
<br />

<br />
Paladins and Shadowknights get Warrior weapon/armor choices but don't get dual wield or most Warrior discs.  Rangers get Warrior weapon choices but don't get most Warrior armor choices or discs.  (Ironically Rangers, the least defensive of the Warrior hybrids, get a better short-term defensive disc than either of the plate hybrid classes.)
<br />

<br />
We fall pretty much in line with the other hybrid classes in the things we inherit from our parent melee class.
<br />

<br />
The Druid confusion may be due to the fact that we originally (a mistake that was eventually corrected) got one strength buff from Druids instead of from the Shaman line.<br />_________________<br />Grimgrey Dorfeater
